<subSubSection id="C30175E2FFA9FFB9C6A45356FE05FD6D" lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="231" pageId="29" pageNumber="230" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFA9FFBAC6A45356FB8CFCAF" blockId="29.[151,1437,613,784]" pageId="29" pageNumber="230">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFA9FFBAC6A45356FE9FFDDF" bold="true" box="[151,274,613,639]" pageId="29" pageNumber="230">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Female. Frons with 3 pairs of supra-antennal setae; apical seta longer than maximum width of palpus; tarsomere 5 shorter than tarsomere 1; setal palisade 2/3 length of mid tibia; setulae below basal half of hind femur shorter than those of anteroventral row of outer half; tergite VI with 3–4 short setulae on each side; sternite VI divided into two oval pieces, with some weak setulae; dorsum of oviscape each side with 5 with short setulae apically and 5 setulae basally; venter of oviscape arrow-shaped, with 2 minute setulae.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF6476E1FFA9FFBAC6A4568DFAD4F85A" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559605" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6559605" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559605/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="230" startId="29.[151,264,1982,2006]" targetBox="[151,1435,805,1956]" targetPageId="29">
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFA9FFBAC6A4568DFAD4F85A" blockId="29.[151,1436,1982,2042]" pageId="29" pageNumber="230">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFA9FFBAC6A4568DFED6F876" bold="true" box="[151,347,1982,2006]" pageId="29" pageNumber="230">FIGURES 21A–F.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C1B5DEAFFA9FFBAC752568DFD6DF877" authority="Liu et Wang" authorityName="Liu et Wang" box="[353,736,1982,2007]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Pseudacteon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="230" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hexasetalis">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFA9FFBAC752568DFDD7F876" box="[353,602,1982,2006]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="230">Pseudacteon hexasetalis</emphasis>
Liu 
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFA9FFBAC4B9568CFD11F876" box="[650,668,1983,2006]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="230">et</emphasis>
Wang
</taxonomicName>
, female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFAAFFB9C6F451A4FD49FEBD" blockId="30.[151,1437,151,897]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFAAFFB9C6F451A4FEA8FF11" bold="true" box="[199,293,151,177]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Female.</emphasis>
Head. Frons (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFAAFFB9C7F751A4FDA4FF11" box="[452,553,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 21" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1982,2006]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,805,1956]" captionTargetId="figure-197@29.[151,1435,805,1956]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 21A–F. Pseudacteon hexasetalis Liu et Wang, female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559605" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559605/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Fig. 21A</figureCitation>
) yellowish brown, with 26 frontal setulae. Frons with 3 pairs of supra-antennal setae, lower pair is proclinate, middle and upper ones reclinate; upper pair higher than lower fronto-orbital setae. Flagellomere 1 pear-shaped and arista brown. Palpus pale yellow, with long setae, apical one longer than maximum width of palpus. Labrium and labella pale yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFAAFFB9C6F45014FD4DFE55" blockId="30.[151,1437,151,897]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">
Thorax. Brown. Scutellum with two pairs of setae, posterior twice length of anterior. Legs yellow. Ratios of lengths of fore tarsomeres about 1.05: 1.01: 0.86: 0.85: 1, with all five bearing a postero-dorsal seta palisade (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFAAFFB9C35C5078FF47FE29" captionStart="FIGURES 21" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1982,2006]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,805,1956]" captionTargetId="figure-197@29.[151,1435,805,1956]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 21A–F. Pseudacteon hexasetalis Liu et Wang, female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559605" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559605/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Fig. 21C</figureCitation>
). Setal palisade extends 2/3 length of mid tibia and comprising 19 modified setulae (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFAAFFB9C2A7505CFB73FE29" box="[1172,1278,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 21" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1982,2006]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,805,1956]" captionTargetId="figure-197@29.[151,1435,805,1956]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 21A–F. Pseudacteon hexasetalis Liu et Wang, female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559605" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559605/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Fig. 21D</figureCitation>
). Setae below basal half of hind femur a little shorter than those of anteroventral row of outer half (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFAAFFB9C25650A0FB41FE0D" box="[1125,1228,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 21" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1982,2006]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,805,1956]" captionTargetId="figure-197@29.[151,1435,805,1956]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 21A–F. Pseudacteon hexasetalis Liu et Wang, female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559605" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559605/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Fig. 21E</figureCitation>
). Wing (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFAAFFB9C31D50A0FA19FE0D" box="[1326,1428,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 21" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1982,2006]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,805,1956]" captionTargetId="figure-197@29.[151,1435,805,1956]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 21A–F. Pseudacteon hexasetalis Liu et Wang, female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559605" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559605/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Fig. 21B</figureCitation>
) length 
<quantity id="4CE38B8CFFAAFFB9C6D05084FE0BFE71" box="[227,390,439,465]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.65" metricValueMax="10.2" metricValueMin="9.1" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" unit="mm" value="0.965" valueMax="1.02" valueMin="0.91">0.91–1.02 mm</quantity>
, width 0.41–0.42, width/length 0.41–0.45. Costal index 0.35–0.36. Costal ratio 1.44: 1. Costal cilia 
<quantity id="4CE38B8CFFAAFFB9C6FD50E9FEB8FE55" box="[206,309,474,501]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" unit="mm" value="0.05">0.05 mm</quantity>
. Alula with 2 setae. Haltere brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFAAFFB9C6F450CCFCD3FD09" blockId="30.[151,1437,151,897]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">
Abdomen. Tergites brown with minute sparse setulae only. Tergites II–V all very much broader than long, but progressively narrowing from tergite II backwards. Tergite VI with 3–4 short setulae on each side (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFAAFFB9C2EE5310FACFFD9E" box="[1245,1346,547,574]" captionStart="FIGURES 26" captionStartId="35.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[220,1379,181,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-19@35.[203,1385,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURES 26A–J. Tergite VI and sternite VI of females.A–B. P. yunnanensis sp. nov.; C–D. P. calceoliformis sp. nov.; E–F. P. hexasetalis Liu et Wang; G–H. P. tianmuensis sp. nov.; I–J. P. parviflavus sp. nov. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559619" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559619/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Fig. 26E</figureCitation>
). Venter grayish brown and segments 1–5 bare. Sternite VI dark brown, with some weak setulae (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFAAFFB9C2B45374FB61FDC2" box="[1159,1260,583,610]" captionStart="FIGURES 26" captionStartId="35.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[220,1379,181,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-19@35.[203,1385,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURES 26A–J. Tergite VI and sternite VI of females.A–B. P. yunnanensis sp. nov.; C–D. P. calceoliformis sp. nov.; E–F. P. hexasetalis Liu et Wang; G–H. P. tianmuensis sp. nov.; I–J. P. parviflavus sp. nov. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559619" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559619/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Fig. 26F</figureCitation>
). Oviscape yellowish brown. The dorsum of the oviscape each side with 5 short setulae apically and 5 setulae basally. The venter of the oviscape arrow-shaped, with 2 minute setulae (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFAAFFB9C4DD53BCFCDCFD09" box="[750,849,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURES 21" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1982,2006]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,805,1956]" captionTargetId="figure-197@29.[151,1435,805,1956]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 21A–F. Pseudacteon hexasetalis Liu et Wang, female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559605" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559605/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Fig. 21F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFAAFFB9C6F45380FE05FD6D" blockId="30.[151,1437,151,897]" box="[199,392,691,717]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFAAFFB9C6F45380FE89FD6D" bold="true" box="[199,260,691,717]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Male</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30175E2FFAAFFB9C6F453E5FD4BFC99" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFAAFFB9C6F453E5FDA1FD52" blockId="30.[151,1437,151,897]" box="[199,556,726,754]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFAAFFB9C6F453E5FEECFD50" bold="true" box="[199,353,726,752]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Distribution.</emphasis>
